# Admin Aside Nav Rule

**When creating a new admin feature (page), add it to the asideNav** in the site config so it appears in the admin sidebar.

## Where to Add

- **Config files:** `public/data/config-*.json` (e.g. `config-capco-design-group.json`, `config-rothco-built-llc.json`)
- **Key:** `asideNav` (array of nav items)
- **Logic:** `src/lib/aside-nav-config.ts` reads nav from `getSiteConfig()` (navigation.aside or asideNav)

## Structure

Top-level link (no children):

```json
{
  "id": "my-feature",
  "label": "My Feature",
  "href": "/admin/my-feature",
  "icon": "star",
  "allow": ["Admin"]
}
```

Child under a section (e.g. Design):

```json
{ "label": "My Component", "href": "/admin/design/my-component" }
```

## DO

- Add new admin pages to `asideNav` in **all site config files** that use the admin
- Use a unique `id` for top-level items
- Set `allow` to control visibility by role (Admin, SuperAdmin, Staff, Client)
- Place design-system/component demos under the Design section's `children`

## DON'T

- Do not create a new admin page without adding it to asideNav—users won't see it in the sidebar
- Do not forget to update all site configs if the feature applies across sites
